WEBVTT

00:01.269 --> 00:03.504
* Da, da, Da-ba-Da, da, da,
Ba-da-Ba-Da-Ba *

00:03.537 --> 00:05.005
* Da, da, Da-ba-Da, da, da
Let's go!

00:05.039 --> 00:06.707
* We'll be there

00:06.740 --> 00:09.377
* A wink and a smile
and a great old time *

00:09.410 --> 00:11.579
* Yeah, we'll be there

00:11.612 --> 00:13.681
* Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found *

00:13.714 --> 00:16.016
* We'll be there
when you turn that corner *

00:16.050 --> 00:17.351
* We'll jump out the bush

00:17.385 --> 00:19.053
* With a big bear hug
and a smile *

00:19.087 --> 00:20.688
* We'll be there

00:27.561 --> 00:29.563
[ Happy music plays ]

00:29.597 --> 00:31.199
Ah!

00:31.232 --> 00:33.834
Alone at last with my delicious
Frosty Fluffs!

00:33.867 --> 00:37.405
So much frosty flavor it makes
me do the freshy dance!

00:37.438 --> 00:38.606
Ooh! [ Laughs ]

00:38.639 --> 00:40.108
Come on, guys.

00:40.141 --> 00:42.543
I think I hear Freshy Bear
doing his freshy dance!

00:42.576 --> 00:44.178
Aha!
Huh?

00:44.212 --> 00:46.247
Better luck next time,
kids!

00:46.280 --> 00:47.848
Whoo! Ahh.

00:47.881 --> 00:49.383
[ Munching ]

00:49.417 --> 00:52.286
I just can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs.

00:52.320 --> 00:54.222
Boy: Frosty Fluffs cereal
is a delicious part

00:54.255 --> 00:56.290
of this complete breakfast!

00:57.758 --> 00:59.227
Grizzly: Hmm.
Where is it?

00:59.260 --> 01:00.861
The lady said
it was on Aisle 6.

01:00.894 --> 01:02.530
-Hmm.
-Wait, here it is!

01:02.563 --> 01:03.764
Go back, go back, go back!

01:03.797 --> 01:05.466
Ooh!
Ooh!Ooh!

01:05.499 --> 01:07.401
Cereal section!

01:07.435 --> 01:08.569
Guys, look!

01:08.602 --> 01:10.238
They have every cereal
here known to mankind.

01:10.271 --> 01:12.806
I feel like I'm in
a corn fructose wonderland.

01:12.840 --> 01:14.608
Ice Bear heart
full of sugar.

01:14.642 --> 01:16.076
We've hit the mother lode, bros.

01:16.110 --> 01:18.279
Now, which one to pick?
There's just so many!

01:18.312 --> 01:20.548
Maybe we could try something
new -- like this one --

01:20.581 --> 01:21.949
Oaky Wheat Flakes.

01:21.982 --> 01:24.418
"Double the oak,
double the wheat"?

01:24.452 --> 01:27.155
Ew! This cereal should be
in the potpourri section.

01:27.188 --> 01:28.789
Hmm.
Oh, I've got it!

01:28.822 --> 01:30.658
We'll pick based on the best
part of the cereal --

01:30.691 --> 01:33.427
the mascot!
Like Teddy Toad for Sugar Snax?

01:33.461 --> 01:36.597
[ Laughs ] Oh, what about
Monsieur Kitty Kat?

01:36.630 --> 01:37.731
Meow!

01:37.765 --> 01:39.066
Ice Bear
prefers Cinna-Bunny.

01:39.099 --> 01:40.668
-Fruity-Bot!
-Nutty Buddy.

01:40.701 --> 01:41.502
Jerry!

01:41.535 --> 01:42.570
[ Laughter ]

01:42.603 --> 01:44.938
[ Gasps ] Oh, my gosh!
Guys, come here!

01:44.972 --> 01:46.440
-What is it?
-It's Frosty Fluffs!

01:46.474 --> 01:48.642
This cereal
has the best mascot!

01:48.676 --> 01:50.144
Oh, man!

01:50.178 --> 01:51.612
I remember that commercial
from when we were kids!

01:51.645 --> 01:53.647
Ice Bear hates children
who steal cereal.

01:53.681 --> 01:55.249
Whoa, wait,
look at this!

01:55.283 --> 01:58.186
They're having a contest
to find a new Freshy Bear!

01:58.219 --> 02:01.522
It says the winner will get to
be in the new commercial!

02:01.555 --> 02:03.857
[ Gasps ] And will win
a lifetime supply

02:03.891 --> 02:05.259
of Frosty Fluffs?!

02:05.293 --> 02:07.295
Ice Bear has never wanted
anything more in life.

02:07.328 --> 02:10.130
You guys, I mean, this contest
was made for us!

02:10.164 --> 02:12.099
I mean, look at us --
we're bears!

02:12.132 --> 02:13.801
Should we still
buy the cereal?

02:13.834 --> 02:15.002
No need, bro.

02:15.035 --> 02:16.136
Once one of us wins,

02:16.170 --> 02:17.638
we'll have free cereal
for life!

02:17.671 --> 02:18.972
Free cereal!

02:19.006 --> 02:20.474
Free cereal.

02:20.508 --> 02:22.810
Ice Bear was going to pay
for that.

02:22.843 --> 02:24.645
* Oom pa, Oom pa

02:24.678 --> 02:27.281
I'm telling you, guys,
we got this in the bag.

02:27.315 --> 02:28.949
This'll be a piece of...
cake?

02:28.982 --> 02:31.819
Together:
I just can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs.

02:31.852 --> 02:33.153
Jeremy, they're ready
for you now.

02:33.187 --> 02:35.189
I just can't bear to be
without my Frost Fluffs.

02:35.223 --> 02:36.990
Man:
Without my Frosty Fluffs.

02:37.024 --> 02:38.192
There's so many people
here, man.

02:38.226 --> 02:39.493
Oh, don't sweat it.

02:39.527 --> 02:41.028
They're probably a bunch
of amateurs.

02:41.061 --> 02:42.530
Come on, let's just
practice our lines.

02:42.563 --> 02:43.997
[ Clears throat ]

02:44.031 --> 02:45.833
I can't bear to be without
my Frosty Fluffs!

02:45.866 --> 02:48.302
Oh, that was good!
Let's see, um...

02:48.336 --> 02:51.472
I can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs!

02:51.505 --> 02:52.706
Nice!

02:52.740 --> 02:54.408
Ice Bear can't bear to be
without his Frosty Fluffs.

02:54.442 --> 02:56.844
Whoa! That's some of the best
bear acting I've ever seen!

02:56.877 --> 02:58.145
You guys
are total naturals.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.580
Oh, thanks, dude!

02:59.613 --> 03:01.215
So do you think one of us
will get the part?

03:01.249 --> 03:02.916
-Oh, yeah, sure.
-Who do you think will get it?

03:02.950 --> 03:06.019
Oh, I mean...
any one of you could, I guess.

03:06.053 --> 03:07.521
Yeah, but if you had
to pick just one.

03:07.555 --> 03:09.189
Woman: Uh, is there
a "Grizzly" here?

03:09.223 --> 03:11.225
Oh, ha ha --
guess I'm up!

03:11.259 --> 03:12.693
-Grizz?
-I'm Grizz!

03:12.726 --> 03:13.894
That's me, it's me --
Grizz.

03:13.927 --> 03:14.928
They're ready
to see you now.

03:14.962 --> 03:15.863
Eee!

03:15.896 --> 03:17.197
Yay!

03:17.231 --> 03:19.267
So do I just...

03:19.300 --> 03:20.868
Just stand there in front of
the camera, on your mark.

03:20.901 --> 03:23.404
So, what's your name?
Tell us a little about yourself.

03:23.437 --> 03:26.206
Uh, hi,
my name is Grizz, um...

03:26.240 --> 03:28.676
I live in a cave,
I know a bunch of karate,

03:28.709 --> 03:31.211
and I'm ready to be
the next Freshy Bear!

03:31.245 --> 03:32.780
What's your name, sir?

03:32.813 --> 03:34.382
Hi, I'm -- I'm Panda.

03:34.415 --> 03:36.284
What are you going to do
for us today, Panda?

03:36.317 --> 03:39.553
Um, I can sing
and dance around.

03:39.587 --> 03:41.389
-Please state your name.
-Ice Bear.

03:41.422 --> 03:43.724
What do you think is your
most bear-like quality?

03:43.757 --> 03:46.226
Ice bear is ice bear.

03:46.260 --> 03:47.628
Okay, Grizz, go ahead
and read your line.

03:47.661 --> 03:50.864
Okay. I can't bear...
I can't bear...

03:50.898 --> 03:52.400
Yeah, okay -- whew.
All right!

03:52.433 --> 03:54.902
I can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs.

03:54.935 --> 03:58.639
Oh, I can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs.

03:58.672 --> 04:01.309
Okay, can you try it
a little cuter?

04:01.342 --> 04:05.245
Oh, I can't bear to be
without my Fwosty Fwuffs.

04:05.279 --> 04:06.780
Go ahead and say the line.

04:06.814 --> 04:08.882
Ice Bear can't bear to be
without his Frosty Fluffs.

04:08.916 --> 04:12.453
No, it's "I can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs."

04:12.486 --> 04:15.055
Ice Bear can't bear to be
without his Frosty Fluffs.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.890
And this is an
Irish Freshy Bear.

04:16.924 --> 04:19.259
[ Irish accent ]
"Oh, I can't bear to be
without me Frosty Fluffs."

04:19.293 --> 04:20.994
And here's Freshy
if he were a cowboy.

04:21.028 --> 04:22.596
"Dag nabbit, I can't stand

04:22.630 --> 04:24.665
to be without
my Frosty Fluffs, partner!"

04:24.698 --> 04:26.233
* Oh, baby

04:26.266 --> 04:28.268
* Ooh, I just
can't bear -- *

04:28.302 --> 04:30.771
Please, just read the line
as it's written.

04:30.804 --> 04:32.606
I...I...

04:32.640 --> 04:34.107
Ice Bear can't bear to be
without his frosty fluffs.

04:34.141 --> 04:35.175
[ Groans ]

04:35.208 --> 04:36.610
Back off you, kids!

04:36.644 --> 04:38.446
Those are
my Frosty Fluffs!

04:38.479 --> 04:42.516
* Frosty Fluuuuuff

04:42.550 --> 04:44.652
Woman:
Okay, give us happy.

04:44.685 --> 04:46.787
All right, now sad.

04:46.820 --> 04:48.689
And let's see
some anger.

04:48.722 --> 04:50.524
[ Creak! ]

04:50.558 --> 04:51.792
[ Humming ]

04:51.825 --> 04:54.862
* Those are my
Frosty Fluffs! *

04:54.895 --> 04:57.164
All right, sir, I think that's
all we need for right now.

04:57.197 --> 04:59.700
You can head back
to the waiting room.

04:59.733 --> 05:01.134
Ice Bear's leg is asleep.

05:01.168 --> 05:03.337
[ Rehearsing lines
indistinctly ]

05:03.371 --> 05:04.972
Okay, everyone listen up.

05:05.005 --> 05:06.306
If I say your name,

05:06.340 --> 05:07.808
we'll need you to come back
tomorrow morning.

05:07.841 --> 05:09.543
Please pick us, please pick us,
please pick us.

05:09.577 --> 05:11.712
Here we are.
Okay -- Grizzly...

05:11.745 --> 05:13.180
-[ Gasps ]
-Panda...

05:13.213 --> 05:15.983
-Yes!
-...and Alonzo Tigerheart.

05:16.016 --> 05:17.351
-Huh?
-Who...?

05:17.385 --> 05:18.819
Ice Bear needed
a stage name.

05:18.852 --> 05:21.121
Wow, those are really
professional, little bro.

05:21.154 --> 05:22.823
Woman: Here are some boxes
of Frosty Fluffs

05:22.856 --> 05:24.291
you can use to rehearse with.

05:24.324 --> 05:25.459
We'll need you here first thing
in the morning.

05:25.493 --> 05:29.096
Bros,
we're gonna be stars!

05:30.498 --> 05:31.732
[ Gulp! ]

05:31.765 --> 05:32.733
Mmm!

05:32.766 --> 05:33.901
[ Growling ]

05:33.934 --> 05:35.302
I can't bear...

05:35.335 --> 05:37.905
I can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs.

05:37.938 --> 05:39.206
Ice Bear
is Freshy Bear.

05:39.239 --> 05:40.374
Ice Bear
is Freshy Bear.

05:40.408 --> 05:41.709
Ice Bear
is Freshy Bear.

05:41.742 --> 05:44.011
Hmm. You're not gonna finish
your cereal?

05:44.044 --> 05:45.546
No, I had
too much already.

05:45.579 --> 05:48.181
Weak, ha!
I already had like 12 bowls.

05:48.215 --> 05:50.083
Well, it's not about
eating a lot, is it?

05:50.117 --> 05:52.252
It is about showing how much
you care about Frosty Fluffs.

05:52.285 --> 05:53.987
Watch this.

05:54.021 --> 05:56.189
[ Serious voice ] I can't bear
to be without my Frosty Fluffs.

05:56.223 --> 05:57.558
[ Normal voice ]
How'd that sound?

05:57.591 --> 05:59.393
[ Grunting ]

05:59.427 --> 06:01.695
Ice Bear can't bear to be
without his Frosty Fluffs.

06:01.729 --> 06:04.398
I can't bear to be without
my Frosty Fluffs!

06:04.432 --> 06:06.066
[ Chuckles ] You guys
kind of say it funny.

06:06.099 --> 06:08.436
Yeah, I'm kind of trying to say
it how a bear would say it.

06:08.469 --> 06:10.037
Ice Bear was channeling
his spirit animal,

06:10.070 --> 06:11.338
which is also a bear.

06:11.371 --> 06:13.373
Eh. It didn't sound
too bear-like.

06:13.407 --> 06:15.543
Oh, come on. We're bears.
How are we not bear-like?

06:15.576 --> 06:17.845
I don't know.
A bear would sound more like...

06:17.878 --> 06:21.348
I can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.784
Ice Bear heard pandas
are raccoons.

06:23.817 --> 06:25.719
-What, is that true?!
-What -- no!

06:25.753 --> 06:28.388
Look, a bunch of scientists
confirmed that pandas are bears,

06:28.422 --> 06:30.891
and I'm pretty sure I'm
the bear-est of all of us.

06:30.924 --> 06:33.594
Come on! What is the
first image you get when
you think about a bear?

06:33.627 --> 06:35.395
Ice bear.
Definitely Ice Bear.

06:35.429 --> 06:37.230
My head immediately got filled
with panda bears

06:37.264 --> 06:38.466
when you said
the word "bear."

06:38.499 --> 06:39.967
Ehh!
You're all wrong!

06:40.000 --> 06:41.902
The answer was grizzly bear,
and that's what I am!

06:41.935 --> 06:44.705
Watch me eat all these
Frosty Fluffs like a true bear!

06:44.738 --> 06:45.806
[ Growling ]

06:45.839 --> 06:47.941
Oh, yeah?
I'm more bear than all of you!

06:47.975 --> 06:50.243
I'll eat anything!
I'll even eat this table!

06:50.277 --> 06:52.312
[ Growling ]

06:52.345 --> 06:55.082
Roar. Roar. Roar.

06:55.115 --> 06:56.750
[ Growling continues ]

06:56.784 --> 06:58.051
Roar. Roar.

06:58.085 --> 06:59.319
[ Growls softly ]

06:59.352 --> 07:00.320
[ Crash! ]

07:00.353 --> 07:02.089
[ Both groan ]

07:02.122 --> 07:03.423
Roar.

07:03.457 --> 07:05.292
You guys are too much
of a distraction.

07:05.325 --> 07:06.594
I'm gonna go
practice alone.

07:06.627 --> 07:08.295
Ice Bear prefers solitude
as well.

07:08.328 --> 07:09.897
Pshh -- like I care.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.098
[ Gobbling ]

07:12.399 --> 07:15.669
Freshy Bear -- Fre-Freshy Bear
can't bear without his...

07:15.703 --> 07:16.937
Frosty Fluffs.

07:16.970 --> 07:18.472
I know, man, okay!

07:18.506 --> 07:19.940
I was just trying
something different.

07:19.973 --> 07:21.408
Leave me alone.

07:21.441 --> 07:23.944
Okay, guys, if you could put
these on, and follow me.

07:23.977 --> 07:26.113
[ Man clears throat ]

07:26.146 --> 07:27.648
Greetings, gentlemen.

07:27.681 --> 07:29.116
[ Beethoven's 9th Symphony
plays ]

07:29.149 --> 07:31.451
I am the director.

07:31.485 --> 07:33.654
All of you should be proud
to be the final candidates

07:33.687 --> 07:35.322
to become
the new Freshy Bear.

07:35.355 --> 07:39.827
I'll know which of you isn't
Freshy Bear -- what is this?

07:39.860 --> 07:41.428
Makeup?
-Um...

07:41.461 --> 07:43.797
No, sir, it's, uh,
like a birthmark.

07:43.831 --> 07:45.265
So you're a raccoon?

07:45.298 --> 07:47.300
You know we're looking
for a bear.

07:47.334 --> 07:49.036
I-I am a bear, sir.

07:49.069 --> 07:50.370
I've got no time for that!

07:50.403 --> 07:52.305
You will prove to me
that you are worthy

07:52.339 --> 07:53.974
of becoming
the next Freshy Bear!

07:54.007 --> 07:55.643
Why did you smile?

07:55.676 --> 07:56.810
Huh? Um, hmm?

07:56.844 --> 07:59.847
Freshy Bear wouldn't smile
or frown for no reason.

07:59.880 --> 08:01.882
I hope you
don't disappoint me

08:01.915 --> 08:04.384
with amateur mistakes
like that, boy.

08:04.417 --> 08:06.486
All right,
show me what you got.

08:06.520 --> 08:08.221
Grizzly, go!
-Yes, sir!

08:08.255 --> 08:09.623
Um, ahem.

08:09.657 --> 08:12.159
I can't bear to be --
-Stop! Panda, go!

08:12.192 --> 08:14.061
I can't --
I can't bear...

08:14.094 --> 08:15.328
-Next!
-Ice Bear ca--

08:15.362 --> 08:16.697
Stop, stop, stop!
[ Sighs ]

08:16.730 --> 08:18.465
Really?
That was Freshy Bear?

08:18.498 --> 08:21.334
That was not Freshy Bear.
That was some sort of...

08:21.368 --> 08:23.003
Trashy Bear!

08:23.036 --> 08:24.805
Freshy Bear is a pop icon.

08:24.838 --> 08:26.974
You'll have to push yourselves
to the limit!

08:27.007 --> 08:28.976
I need to see what
you're capable of!

08:29.009 --> 08:31.011
Okay, so, what do you
want us to do?

08:31.044 --> 08:32.746
Freshy Bear does a dance.

08:32.780 --> 08:36.183
I need to see
your best bear dance.

08:36.216 --> 08:38.986
[ Upbeat pop music plays ]

08:39.019 --> 08:41.689
[ Grunting ]

08:50.230 --> 08:53.333
* Dare to be flaunting

08:53.366 --> 08:56.236
* Jump into motion, baby

08:56.269 --> 08:57.404
Hey!

08:57.437 --> 08:58.739
* Keep 'em stepping with it

08:58.772 --> 09:02.375
* Don't care what they say,
yeah *

09:02.409 --> 09:03.711
Hmm.

09:03.744 --> 09:05.879
Oh, it's perfect.
* Dare to be workin'

09:05.913 --> 09:09.082
* All up through your youth

09:09.116 --> 09:11.551
* Try to be moving

09:11.585 --> 09:12.920
* It's cool, it's smooth

09:12.953 --> 09:14.788
Get out of the way!
It's not your turn!

09:14.822 --> 09:16.223
[ Grunting ]

09:16.256 --> 09:19.259
* Tell your crew that
I'm working past midnight *

09:19.292 --> 09:20.628
* Gonna rock it till...

09:20.661 --> 09:22.896
I can't bear to be
without my Frosty Fluffs!

09:22.930 --> 09:24.197
Roar, roar!

09:24.231 --> 09:25.432
[ Laughs ]

09:25.465 --> 09:26.967
What the --

09:27.000 --> 09:28.568
[ Grunting ]

09:28.602 --> 09:32.072
* Tell your crew that
I'm working past midnight *

09:32.105 --> 09:35.375
* I'm gonna rock it
till there's no tomorrow *

09:35.408 --> 09:37.611
Oh, ho, ho, yes!
Bravo!

09:37.645 --> 09:40.480
* Right now

09:40.513 --> 09:41.982
[ Laughs ]

09:42.015 --> 09:43.751
Yes, yes!

09:43.784 --> 09:45.485
I gotta say,
you guys were all great.

09:45.518 --> 09:47.821
Man, this is going to be
a difficult choice.

09:47.855 --> 09:50.123
But there can only be
one Freshy Bear,

09:50.157 --> 09:51.825
so I have made
my decision.

09:51.859 --> 09:52.893
Panda!

09:52.926 --> 09:55.295
[ Gasps, laughs ]
What, seriously?

09:55.328 --> 09:56.630
Your face!

09:56.664 --> 09:58.398
You look too much
like a raccoon.

09:58.431 --> 09:59.833
Huh?
[ Laughs ]

09:59.867 --> 10:02.269
Grizzly, really impressive
dance moves,

10:02.302 --> 10:03.771
but a little too trashy.

10:03.804 --> 10:06.006
-What -- I wasn't trashy!
-Alonzo!

10:06.039 --> 10:08.275
You...were just weird.

10:08.308 --> 10:09.910
Ice Bear's dance
was fresh to death.

10:09.943 --> 10:12.445
Well, then who gets to be
the new Freshy Bear?

10:12.479 --> 10:15.448
Oh, I've got to say you guys
were super close.

10:15.482 --> 10:17.017
But not close enough.

10:17.050 --> 10:19.486
So I am honored and happy
to announce

10:19.519 --> 10:22.155
that the new Freshy Bear
is going to be...

10:22.189 --> 10:23.691
me!
What?!

10:23.724 --> 10:25.993
I'd like to thank all of you
for letting me realize

10:26.026 --> 10:28.662
that I'm the only one suited
for this sophisticated role.

10:28.696 --> 10:30.597
Oh, I'm gonna be so perfect!

10:30.630 --> 10:32.299
Kids are going to love me!

10:32.332 --> 10:34.267
Okay, thanks again
for coming, guys.

10:34.301 --> 10:37.270
Please show these gentlemen to
the exit, please, thank you!

10:37.304 --> 10:38.505
[ Door slams ]

10:38.538 --> 10:40.307
Does that mean
we're not gonna get

10:40.340 --> 10:42.009
our lifetime supply
of cereal?

10:42.042 --> 10:44.611
[ Munching ]

10:44.644 --> 10:45.979
